HEADWORD: Wire-tailed
<hw>Wire"-tailed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having some or all of the tail quills terminated in a long,
slender, pointed shaft, without a web or barbules.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

